.TH COGENI 1 "February 2026" "0.1.0" "cogeni Manual"
.SH NAME
cogeni \- A language-agnostic code generation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cogeni
[\fIFILES\fR...]
.br
.B cogeni ast
\fIFILE\fR [\fB\-\-lang\fR \fILANG\fR]
.br
.B cogeni clean
[\fIFILES\fR...]
.br
.B cogeni diff
[\fIFILES\fR...]
.br
.B cogeni run
[\fISCRIPT.lua\fR] [\fB\-e\fR \fICODE\fR]
.br
.B cogeni completion
[\fIbash|zsh|fish|powershell\fR]
.br
.B cogeni show dependency-graph
[\fIENTRY.lua\fR]
.br
.B cogeni repl
.br
.B cogeni config show
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cogeni
is a tool designed to automate code generation by executing Lua scripts embedded directly within your source files. It leverages Tree-sitter for high-fidelity AST parsing and JQ for declarative data querying. It features parallel execution, automatic dependency tracking, and atomic filesystem commits.
.SH CORE WORKFLOW
The tool operates in three distinct phases:
.TP
1. \fBExtraction\fR
Scans the file for \fB<cogeni>\fR blocks. It identifies and strips comment prefixes (e.g., "# ", "// ", "-- ") from each line within the block to assemble a valid Lua script.
.TP
2. \fBExecution\fR
Runs the assembled script in a specialized Lua environment. The script can parse the host file (or others) using \fBcogeni.read_ast\fR and capture output using the \fBwrite(id, content)\fR global function.
.TP
3. \fBReplacement\fR
Locates \fB<generated by="cogeni" id="ID">\fR blocks and replaces their entire content with the strings registered via \fBwrite\fR. If the new content matches the existing content, the file remains untouched.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B [default]
Processes the provided file(s) for generation blocks and commits changes to disk. If no files are provided, it looks for \fBcogeni.lua\fR in the current directory.
.TP
.B ast \fIFILE\fR
Dumps the Tree-sitter AST of the specified file as JSON.
.TP
.B clean [\fIFILES\fR...]
Empties all \fB<generated>\fR blocks in the specified files. Useful for resetting a project state.
.TP
.B diff [\fIFILES\fR...]
Performs a dry-run of the generation and shows a unified diff of the changes that would be made.
.TP
.B run [\fISCRIPT.lua\fR]
Executes a Lua script. Useful for project-wide orchestration. If no script is provided, it looks for \fBcogeni.lua\fR.
.TP
.B completion [\fIbash|zsh|fish|powershell\fR]
Generates shell completion scripts for Bash, Zsh, Fish, and PowerShell.
.TP
.B show dependency-graph [\fIENTRY.lua\fR]
Visualizes the execution and file dependency tree discovered during processing.
.TP
.B config show
Displays the current configuration, including grammar mappings and custom sources.
.SH TAGS
.TP
.B <cogeni> ... </cogeni>
Container for the generator script.
.TP
.B <generated by="cogeni" id="ID"> ... </cogeni>
Target for code injection. The closing tag is \fB</cogeni>\fR.
.SH CONFIGURATION
\fBcogeni\fR looks for \fBconfig.yaml\fR in standard XDG locations (e.g., \fB~/.config/cogeni/\fR).
.PP
Example configuration:
.nf
grammar:
  location: /path/to/grammars
  mapping:
    .custom: python
  sources:
    sql:
      url: https://github.com/DerekStride/tree-sitter-sql
      branch: gh-pages
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate code for a Python file:
\fBcogeni models.py\fR
.TP
See what changes would be made:
\fBcogeni diff .\fR
.TP
Orchestrate a whole project:
\fBcogeni run cogeni.lua\fR
.SH TIPS
.IP \(bu 2
Use the \fBrepl\fR command to experiment with JQ queries and Lua scripts in real-time.
.IP \(bu 2
Combine \fBcogeni ast\fR with external tools like \fBgrep\fR or \fBjq\fR to quickly find the node types you need to target.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cogeni-lua (7)
